    "Html": "<p id=eff42bf0-c6f9-012c-54a5-12313b03045a>Hi</p>\r\n<p id=eff43cf0-c6f9-012c-54a6-12313b03045a>Some time ago, I <a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman/2009/01/29/how-to-show-large-amounts-of-data-in-wpf-using-ui-virtualization/\">blogged</a> about a similar issue that could be reproduced with the UIComposition QS, and provided a fix for it. You might find it useful.</p>\r\n<p id=eff44de0-c6f9-012c-54a7-12313b03045a>Please let me know if this helps.</p>\r\n<p id=eff45f00-c6f9-012c-54a8-12313b03045a>Damian Schenkelman    <br><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman\">http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman</a></p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-12-09T06:20:39.613-08:00",
